Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist
Never share your UPI PIN, OTP, or banking details with anyone—even if they claim to be from a bank.
Remember: You do NOT need a PIN to receive money on UPI—only to send it.
Always verify UPI collect requests before approving; check the sender’s name carefully.
Avoid clicking on unknown links received via SMS, email, or WhatsApp.
Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) on all important accounts (email, banking, social media).
Use strong and unique passwords; avoid using the same password across multiple platforms.
Install apps only from official app stores (Google Play Store / App Store).
Do not use public Wi-Fi for financial transactions or logging into sensitive accounts.
Regularly update your phone and apps to fix security vulnerabilities.
Be cautious of urgent or “too good to be true” offers (prizes, jobs, discounts).
